body: Can you please comment this line and tell me if it runs? I've never tested it for python2.7
I removed the debug line anyway.

It works for python 3.x. Thank you.

Even if the line is commented, it does not work for python 2.6
Please let me if there is any possible solution for python 2.6.
Hum I'm not sure how difficult it would be. Python 2.x is going to be decommissioned soon anyway.

You should probably be clearer on the landing page that this library works best in Python 3. When I tried to load a TCN in Keras using Python 2.7.15 it gave the following error:
```
File "/usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tcn/__init__.py", line 1, in <module> \
    from tcn.tcn import TCN, compiled_tcn
  File "/usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tcn/tcn.py", line 225
    print(f'model.x = {input_layer.shape}')
                                         ^
SyntaxError: invalid syntax
```

I then installed in Python 3 and re-ran, and it works fine.
@lingdoc yep thank you I'm going to do that!

Seem to be getting the same error in Python 3:
```
File "/usr/local/lib/python3.5/dist-packages/tcn/tcn.py", line 221
    print(f'model.x = {input_layer.shape}')
```
Nevermind, I see the f-string was introduced in 3.6. I unfortunately am stuck with 3.5 for now so I can just modify the module as needed. Thanks for all your work on this!
@nhirons I can push a release without the f string!

```
pip install keras-tcn --upgrade # (2.7.1)
```

Enjoy!
